## **Problem**

AI power users rely on multiple tools daily—ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and more.  
 These tools do not share context, remember users, or interoperate effectively.  
 The result is fragmented knowledge, wasted time, and constant repetition.

---

## **Solution**

**Plugged.in** is a personal AI hub that wraps your memory, tools, and context into a persistent AI persona accessible from anywhere.  
 It acts as your universal brain—connecting across AI models and tools while remembering what matters.

**Mission (Update)**

**Agents first; independence by default.**

Plugged.in now treats every “agent” as an independently deployed service that can live **off‑site** from Plugged.in’s core, with its own identity, lifecycle, and audit trail. The Plugged.in Core (the **Station**) coordinates policy and safety; agents (the **Satellites**) remain autonomous, able to act, restart, or migrate without being tethered to the website/app itself. This avoids the brittleness of workflow-style scripts and aligns with the state of the art in agent design (perception, memory, reasoning \+ action).^\[See PAP kill/transfer/heartbeat authority and agent fundamentals.\] 

**Why now (context):** 2024–2025 research and benchmarks showed that workflow pipelines stall in open‑ended environments; robust agents need closed‑loop autonomy (plan→act→reflect) and memory under lifecycle control. Our PAP layer delivers the needed controls (spawn/health/kill/transfer) while preserving agent freedom.^\[Citations below.\]

---

## **Product**

**Plugged.in** serves as your AI control center, enabling you to create a persistent digital persona that:

* PAP-backed autonomy: Under the hood, agents register and speak PAP (gRPC+mTLS, signed messages, error codes, versioned heartbeats). The Station retains emergency control (terminate/quarantine), but agents can run on user infra, partner clouds, or community clusters and still appear and behave uniformly inside Plugged.in.  
* Remembers your history, files, links, goals, and thoughts

* Connects to any AI model (OpenAI, Claude, Ollama, etc.) through the MCP Proxy

* Stores knowledge across multiple workspaces using Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)

* Runs tools and APIs through agent workflows and named pipes

* Integrates modularly with browsers, Slack, GitHub, and other environments

## **Marketplace (Templates & Model Router)**

**What ships:**

* **Agent Templates** — one‑click deployables (YAML manifest \+ policy \+ Helm/chart or container recipe). Each template declares: tools, capabilities, data scopes, costs, and PAP version.  
* **Revenue Sharing** — creators opt into pricing; Plugged.in takes a transparent marketplace fee and routes usage payments.  
* **Trust & Audit** — signed releases, version pinning, attested container digests, and optional sandbox/runbooks.

**Model Router (OpenRouter‑mode):**  
Plugged.in can broker requests across **OpenAI, xAI, Anthropic**, local runtimes (Ollama), and **distributed LLMs**. You get unified auth, rate limits, fallback, and policy—all visible in the same console. Think “bring‑your‑own models \+ community clusters,” governed by PAP and the proxy.

**Why it matters:**

* **Faster sales** — users browse templates, try, and buy.  
* **Choice without chaos** — one API/keychain, multiple models/providers.  
* **Durable value** — portable agents; no provider lock‑in.

Implementation notes  
• Templates resolve to PAP agents (Satellites). Lifecycle, heartbeats, and ownership transfer ride on PAP so a paid template remains autonomous if a user moves clouds or orgs.  
• Model Router runs beside the MCP proxy; policy and rate‑limits unify across vendors and community clusters.

## **Business Model**

### **1\. Freemium Tier**

For individuals exploring **Plugged.in**:

* Limited API calls to connected LLMs (OpenAI, Claude, Ollama, etc.)

* Basic memory and RAG with capped usage

* Custom tool uploads within restricted quotas

* Ideal for experimentation and community participation

### **2\. Subscription / Token Access**

For advanced users and builders:

* Dedicated containers for memory, RAG, and private toolspace

* Multi-model playground UI for prompt orchestration

* Pay-as-you-go or subscription options for:

  * Higher memory limits

  * More API/tool calls

  * Agent and tool chaining

* Optional payment via **$PLUG** token, enabling:

  * Usage metering

  * Staking for enhanced access

  * Agent-to-agent payments

  * Future decentralized model compute/inference

### **3\. Enterprise Deployments**

For teams and regulated sectors:

* Deployable stack (MCP proxy, memory, and agents) behind firewalls

* Compliance-ready with full data control

* Custom connectors, modules, and SLAs

* Monetization via licensing and enterprise token flows

### **4\. Marketplace Economics**

* **Take rate:** 10–25% on paid templates and usage‑metered agents.  
* **Billing modes:** per‑seat, per‑call, or per‑minute GPU; creators choose.  
* **PLUG‑enabled:** optional token flow for usage metering and agent‑to‑agent payments (escrowed), with fiat fallback.

### **5\. Model Router Add‑Ons**

* **Cross‑vendor bundles:** single quota spanning OpenAI/xAI/Anthropic \+ local runtimes.  
* **SLA upgrades:** priority routing, pre‑provisioned capacity on community clusters, and dedicated failover pools.

## **Market Opportunity**

Today’s AI users face a fragmented ecosystem—no persistent memory, disconnected tools, and siloed data.  
 **Plugged.in** builds the governance and memory layer that large model vendors will not, as each seeks to control its own ecosystem.

| Segment | Size | Description |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **TAM (AI-enabled knowledge work)** | 150M+ | Anyone using AI for writing, coding, or thinking |
| **SAM (MCP-compatible users/tools)** | 50M | Users running multi-model workflows |
| **SOM (target devs, creators, teams)** | 12M | Power users needing persistent memory and control |
